In this Episode: 10 Cool Mac Keyboard Shortcuts
- Series 1

00:00:08.029 --> 00:00:13.099
OS X offers lots of cool keyboard shortcut
commands...too many to mention in just one

00:00:13.099 --> 00:00:18.510
series. Therefore I'll be making a collection
of Series each showing 10 Cool Keyboard Shortcuts

00:00:18.510 --> 00:00:22.039
that you might find interesting....On to Series
1:

00:00:22.039 --> 00:00:24.099
So...Let's Get Started

00:00:24.099 --> 00:00:25.740
And in no particular order

00:00:25.740 --> 00:00:28.740
Number 1: Cluttered Desktop...no problem,
pressing:

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:34.770
ctrl + opt + cmd + 6 makes them all align
to the Right-hand side of your display.

00:00:34.770 --> 00:00:40.200
Number 2: Open Applications or Utilities or
Desktop Folders by pressing:

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:45.230
cmd + shift + either the letters A/U/ or D

00:00:45.230 --> 00:00:50.520
Number 3: Open a New Window.
For the following Applications: Finder, Safari

00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:52.500
and Maps, by pressing:

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:54.770
cmd + N

00:00:54.770 --> 00:01:00.120
Number 4: Force Quit Any Application that
maybe acting up by pressing:

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:05.600
opt + cmd + esc

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:10.859
Number 5: Close All Windows that belongs to
a particular Application, for example, if

00:01:10.859 --> 00:01:16.320
you have a few windows opened for the following
Application, Finder, Safari and Maps, pressing:

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:19.020
opt + cmd + W

00:01:19.020 --> 00:01:23.149
Will close all opened windows belonging to
a particular Application.

00:01:23.149 --> 00:01:26.969
Number 6: Create a New Folder within a Folder
by pressing:

00:01:26.969 --> 00:01:29.609
shift + cmd + N

00:01:29.609 --> 00:01:35.490
For example you can be in the Desktop, Documents,
Downloads Folder...basically any Folder..pressing

00:01:35.490 --> 00:01:40.299
shift + cmd + N will create a new folder.

00:01:40.299 --> 00:01:45.639
Number 7: Quick Look:
Pressing cmd + Y or just the spacebar ( I

00:01:45.639 --> 00:01:51.270
personally prefer spacebar) gives you a quick
look of a file...press again to close.

00:01:51.270 --> 00:01:57.159
For example..any picture, document, video,
music...practically anything gives you a quick

00:01:57.159 --> 00:02:00.639
preview, you can then decide if you wish to
open it.

00:02:00.639 --> 00:02:05.039
Number 8: Make all Windows disappear to all
sides of the display by pressing:

00:02:05.039 --> 00:02:09.290
cmd + F3 Abracadabra...All Gone...yeah Pops...I'm
starting my Homework.

00:02:09.290 --> 00:02:12.080
Press again to bring them all back...shazaam!

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:15.740
Number 9: Cycle through Opened Applications
by pressing:

00:02:15.740 --> 00:02:22.240
cmd + Tab to cycle Forward or shift + cmd
+ Tab to cycle Backwards.

00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:26.030
Number 10: Just for Fun..."Let's See That
in Slow-Motion! Or " Let's See That in Slo-Mo"

00:02:26.030 --> 00:02:31.690
Whist in DashBoard, Mission Control or the
Desktop press the shift key and release after

00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:37.060
clicking on minimize, maximize or even adding
or deleting Gadgets.

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:44.060
minimizing or maximizing a windows begins
slo-mo.

00:02:49.230 --> 00:02:54.450
For example in:

00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:57.930
DashBoard....Mission Control...Desktop

